        <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="70" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL">[quote]
It goes deeper than just that.  This will seem like I am defending Verant, but in the end you will see I am not.

Test Server has several modifications.  Different way to enter the game (different .exe file) etc...

Just because something works there, and I have no doubt it does, doesn't mean there won't be conflicts on a "standard" server.  The BEST possible way for them to test these things is to open a test server #2.  Test server #1 is the current server (or cluster as the case most likely is), and test #2 is a "standard" server, but used by the general public (probably allow us to automaticaly log our toons in there as well as our normal server just to make us at least be willing to try it out rather than force us have to start over again just to help them make a better product).  If something does well on Test server #1, it is implimented on test server #2 and a message is made (like the ones just after logging in) informing us of the new patch to test #2.  I would hope they can track which server you spend your time on (helps to dictate what servers get priority upgrades to bandwidth, etc..) and make an offer.  Test #2 players who log in knowing they may have issues to help make the game better get a reduced monthly rate after playing X ammount of hours on the Test #2 server (assuming there is something big like the new UI changes comming down).

In this scenario, you get a large ammount of tests allowing for thousands of possibly driver/hardware combos making for a very thorough test of the changes that has also taken place in the environment it will be implimented on (which is why for this system to work the test #2 cluster MUST be the EXACT same as a standard server).

Unfortunately, what would a computer technician know compared to verant about software testing?

Just so you all know, I am doing the cut paste thing here to send to rich.  Hopefully after he has some time to breathe, he will read the email and pass it on to his superiors.



Death Takes on many faces, yours takes on mine. 
Lizalfos Deathscale
http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=311916
Blood Red Rose
Tarew Marr
[/quote]</textarea><br>
        </td>
